Mononuclear cell infiltrates are characteristic of [[Inflammation|inflammatory]] lesions, where white blood cells, mainly [[macrophages]] and [[lymphocytes]], collect at the site of injury to help clear away the debris. It is the sign of onset of [[graft rejection]].

